{
  "stem": "27340.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I realized, particularly having been in that unit, that it was very important to get a-- a basic degree in engineering.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And while I was offered a place at the Technion, which is the Technical University in Haifa, I felt rather worried about this, and I'll tell you quite honestly why.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was never a terribly good student.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the combination of the material, which was tough, with a foreign language, which I spoke but had great difficulties in writing or reading-- because I learned the language via the ears, by hearing it, by speaking it, and so on-- I thought it would be easier if I could do that back in England.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so I wrote to the Dean of the faculty of the college at which I studied early on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was called The Northampton College of Advanced Technology in those days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Today it's called the City University.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it's part of London University.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Today, it's a university in its own right, but in those days it was attached to the University of London, yes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would go back there as a part time student purely and simply because I couldn't afford to maintain myself without having any income.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from an engineering point of view, that was good, because while you learned the theoretical part in the evenings, you actually executed the practical aspects during the day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was the finest combination you could possibly have.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was tough.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It lasted six, seven years, but it was worth it in the end.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Dean was very appreciative.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He remembered me well because I was quite an outstanding bloke before I left.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I scored one mark in the mathematics paper, and so I went down in the annals of the college history.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
